function (uint16,string memory,string memory,uint8,uint32,contract IERC20Token[] memory,uint32[] memory) returns (contract IConverter)

acceptOwnership().details: used by a new owner to accept an ownership transfer

addConverter(address).details: adds an existing converter to the registry can only be called by the owner

getAnchor(uint256).details: returns the converter anchor at a given index

returns._0: anchor at the given index

getAnchorCount().details: returns the number of converter anchors in the registry

returns._0: number of anchors

getAnchors().details: returns the list of converter anchors in the registry

returns._0: list of anchors

getConvertersByAnchors(address[]).details: returns a list of converters for a given list of anchors this is a utility function that can be used to reduce the number of calls to the contract

returns._0: list of converters

getConvertibleToken(uint256).details: returns the convertible token at a given index

returns._0: convertible token at the given index

getConvertibleTokenAnchor(address,uint25.details: returns the converter anchor associated with a given convertible token at a given index

returns._0: anchor associated with the given convertible token at the given index

getConvertibleTokenAnchorCount(address).details: returns the number of converter anchors associated with a given convertible token

returns._0: number of anchors associated with the given convertible token

getConvertibleTokenAnchors(address).details: returns the list of aoncerter anchors associated with a given convertible token

returns._0: list of anchors associated with the given convertible token

getConvertibleTokenCount().details: returns the number of convertible tokens in the registry

returns._0: number of convertible tokens

getConvertibleTokens().details: returns the list of convertible tokens in the registry

returns._0: list of convertible tokens

getLiquidityPool(uint256).details: returns the liquidity pool at a given index

returns._0: liquidity pool at the given index

getLiquidityPoolByConfig(uint16,address[.details: searches for a liquidity pool with specific configuration

params._type: converter type, see ConverterBase contract main doc

returns._0: the liquidity pool, or zero if no such liquidity pool exists

getLiquidityPoolCount().details: returns the number of liquidity pools in the registry

returns._0: number of liquidity pools

getLiquidityPools().details: returns the list of liquidity pools in the registry

returns._0: list of liquidity pools

isAnchor(address).details: checks whether or not a given value is a converter anchor

returns._0: true if the given value is an anchor, false if not

isConverterValid(address).details: checks whether or not a given converter is valid

returns._0: true if the given converter is valid, false if not

isConvertibleToken(address).details: checks whether or not a given value is a convertible token

returns._0: true if the given value is a convertible token, false if not

isConvertibleTokenAnchor(address,address.details: checks whether or not a given value is a converter anchor of a given convertible token

returns._0: true if the given value is an anchor of the given convertible token, false if not

isLiquidityPool(address).details: checks whether or not a given value is a liquidity pool

returns._0: true if the given value is a liquidity pool, false if not

isSimilarLiquidityPoolRegistered(address.details: checks if a liquidity pool with given configuration is already registered

returns._0: if a liquidity pool with the same configuration is already registered

newConverter(uint16,string,string,uint8,.details: creates a zero supply liquid token / empty liquidity pool and adds its converter to the registry

params._type: converter type, see ConverterBase contract main doc

returns._0: new converter

removeConverter(address).details: removes a converter from the registry anyone can remove an existing converter from the registry, as long as the converter is invalid note that the owner can also remove valid converters

restrictRegistryUpdate(bool).details: restricts the permission to update the contract-registry

params._onlyOwnerCanUpdateRegistry: indicates whether or not permission is restricted to owner only

transferOwnership(address).details: allows transferring the contract ownership the new owner still needs to accept the transfer can only be called by the contract owner
